    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="91"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.4212Anti-War/42</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Canada</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Baldwin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1928</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received July 19.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 529</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Legation’s telegrams No. 155 of
                    July 17, 2 p.m., and No. 156 of July 17, 4 p.m.,<note n="95" xml:id="d91fn95"
                        >Neither printed.</note> I have the honor to transmit herewith enclosed a
                    copy of a note received from W. L. Mackenzie King, Secretary of State for
                    External Affairs, stating that His Majesty’s Government in Canada cordially
                    accepts the Treaty as revised and is prepared to participate in its
                    signature.</p>
                <pb facs="0239" n="111" xml:id="pg_111"/>
                <p>Since the Canadian Government does not desire that its reply be published before
                    that of the British Government, it has been agreed that the Canadian reply will
                    be released for publication in the morning newspapers of Thursday, July 19.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">La Verne Baldwin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Enclosure]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Canadian Secretary of State for External Affairs</hi>
                            (<persName type="from">
                            <hi rend="italic">Mackenzie King</hi>
                        </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the American Minister</hi> (<persName
                            type="to">
                            <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-16">
                                <hi rend="italic">16 July, 1928</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I desire to acknowledge your note of June
                        23rd and the revised draft which it contained of the Treaty for the
                        Renunciation of War, and to state that His Majesty’s Government in Canada
                        cordially accepts the Treaty as revised and is prepared to participate in
                        its signature.</p>
                    <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">W. L. Mackenzie King</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
